0.%20This%20was%20at%20par%20with%20Express%20Train%20fares.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpassenger-trains-express-railway-fares%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indian%20bizman%20donates%20Rs%202.25cr%20for%20release%20of%20900%20prisoners%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709033708000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108044629%2Cimgsize-1169700.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fas-pre-ramzan-gesture-indian-businessman-donates-rs-2-25-crore-for-release-of-900-prisoners%2Farticleshow%2F108044460.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F108044460.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EDubai-based%20Indian%20businessman%20Firoz%20Merchant%20of%20Pure%20Gold%20donated%20Rs%202.25%20crore%20to%20release%20900%20prisoners%20from%20Gulf%20jails%20in%20Dubai%2C%20Arabian%20nation.%20The%20Forgotten%20Society%20initiative%2C%20founded%20by%20Merchant%2C%20has%20secured%20the%20release%20of%2020%2C000%20prisoners.%20Colonel%20Mohammed%20Yusuf%20Al-Matrooshi%20praised%20Merchant's%20efforts.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fas-pre-ramzan-gesture-indian-businessman-donates-rs-2-25-crore-for-release-of-900-prisoners%2Farticleshow%2F108044460.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fas-pre-ramzan-gesture-indian-businessman-donates-rs-2-25-crore-for-release-of-900-prisoners%2Famp_articleshow%2F108044460.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fas-pre-ramzan-gesture-indian-businessman-donates-rs-2-25-crore-for-release-of-900-prisoners%2Famp_articleshow%2F108044460.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22MSP%20for%20Farmers%3A%20Does%20India%20Need%20to%20Look%20Westwards%20for%20a%20Solution%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25131354%2Ffarmer-1.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20government%20and%20farmers%20are%20battling%20each%20other%20on%20Punjab-Haryana%20borders%20over%20the%20right%20to%20fair%20price%2C%20we%20need%20to%20ask%20the%20question%20%E2%80%93%20how%20will%20the%20minimum%20price%20floors%20be%20implemented%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinancially%20speaking%20there%20is%20a%20consensus%20of%20a%20requirement%20of%20Rs%201.5%20lakh%20crore%20as%20financial%20support%2C%20but%20agriculturally%20speaking%20how%20will%20the%20system%20work%3F%20The%20%E2%80%98New%20Deal%20Farm%E2%80%99%20programme%20from%20the%20US%20may%20have%20a%20potential%20answer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20origin%20of%20Minimum%20Support%20Price%20(MSP)%20idea%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20Dr%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Fthe-men-behind-apmc-msp-and-procurement-6617277%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520origin%2520of%2520MSPs%2520or%2CMinistry%2520of%2520Food%2520and%2520Agriculture.%5C%22%3EFrank%20Parker%20of%20USAID%20who%20gave%20the%20MSP%3C%2Fa%3E%20idea%20to%20the%20Indian%20government.%20He%20suggested%20the%20price%20floors%20drawing%20from%20an%20FDR%20(Franklin%20Roosevelt)%20New%20Deal%20agrarian%20policy%20that%20transformed%20rural%20America%20and%20increased%20farmers%20net%20income%20by%20115%25%20in%2010%20years%20between%201942%20and%201952.%20This%20was%20a%20golden%20period%20not%20just%20for%20the%20farmers%2C%20the%20industry%20got%20raw%20materials%20for%20fair%20price%20and%20consumers%20were%20not%20pinched%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20parity%20system%20was%20built%20on%20price%20floors%20(minimum%20and%20ceiling%20floors)%2C%20growing%20quota%2C%20government%20grain%20reserves%20and%20co-operative%20and%20individual%20systems%20for%20growing%20quotas%2C%20among%20other%20things.%20Instead%20of%20losing%20money%2C%20the%20government%20gained%20revenue%20and%20also%20directly%20added%20to%20rural%20American%20economy.%20The%20vestiges%20of%20the%20same%20idea%20are%20still%20embodied%20in%20our%20agrarian%20and%20food%20institutions%20likes%20MSP%2C%20Food%20Corporation%20of%20India%20(FCI)%2C%20National%20Agricultural%20Cooperative%20Marketing%20Federation%20(NAFED)%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFDR%E2%80%99s%20New%20Deal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20farmers%20were%20destroyed%20by%20the%20summer%20of%20the%201920.%20By%20June%2C%20prices%20from%20corn%20to%20hogs%20all%20had%20crashed%2C%20ending%20the%20World%20War%20I%20high%20demand%20and%20high%20prices.%20For%20instance%2C%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20five%20months%20the%20price%20of%20corn%C2%A0fell%20from%20%241.83%2Fbushel%20to%20less%20than%2070%20cents%2Fbushel%20at%20the%20Chicago%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThousands%20of%20farming%20families%20were%20foreclosed%20and%20rural%20America%20was%20battling%20over%20production%20given%20that%20more%20land%20was%20brought%20under%20agriculture%20under%20during%20World%20War%20I%20years.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20area%20under%20wheat%20had%20increased%20from%2048%20million%20acres%20in%201914%20to%20over%2075%20million%20by%201919.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20crash%2C%20rural%20America%20was%20being%20plagued%20by%20hyperinflation%20on%20land%20prices%2C%20speculation%20and%20excessive%20debt.%20Meanwhile%2C%20by%201922%20American%20agricultural%20exports%20had%20fallen%20to%20the%20value%20of%20%241%2C883%2C315%2C000%3B%2050%25%20decrease%20from%201919.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20prices%20didn%E2%80%99t%20rise%20again%20for%20a%20long%20time%20as%20by%201929%20the%20Great%20Depression%20had%20rocked%20the%20economy.%20In%20over%20production%2C%20supply%20mismanagement%20and%20falling%20incomes%2C%20rural%20America%20was%20almost%20on%20the%20precipice%20for%20collapse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20is%20best%20described%20in%20a%20letter%20%E2%80%93%20pleading%20for%20a%20farm%20debt%20moratorium%20%E2%80%93%20to%20then%20agriculture%20secretary%20Henry%20C%20Wallace%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhy%20should%20we%20all%20have%20our%20homes%20taken%20from%20us%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20Georgia%20sharecropper%20wrote%20to%20the%20Agriculture%20Secretary%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20fall%20not%20only%20will%20i%20lose%20my%20home%20and%20everything%20in%20it%2C%20but%20hundreds%2C%20perhaps%20thousands%2C%20will%20be%20in%20my%20conditions%2C%20homeless.%20Unless%2C%20the%20farmers%20gets%2035c%20to%2040c%20for%20his%20cotton%2C%20we%20will%20be%20ruined%E2%80%A6.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20prevent%20a%20rural%20meltdown%20Franklin%20Roosevelt%E2%80%99s%20government%20introduced%20a%20New%20Deal%20for%20farmers%20built%20upon%20price%20floors%2C%20grain%20reserves%20and%20recourse%20loans.%20It%20began%20with%20key%20agricultural%20commodities%20like%20corn%20(1933)%2C%20cotton%20(1933)%2C%20wheat%2C%20tobacco%20(1937)%20and%20then%20even%20spread%20into%20the%20meat%2C%20poultry%2C%20fresh%20vegetables%20and%20to%20even%20dairy%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-in-tight-spot-over-fresh-round-of-farmers-protest-reconciliation-with-akali-dal-on-back-burner%5C%22%3EBJP%20in%20Tight%20Spot%20Over%20Fresh%20Round%20of%20Farmers%20Protest%2C%20Reconciliation%20With%20Akali%20Dal%20on%20Back%20Burner%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20an%20agricultural%20policy%20perspective%2C%20the%20period%20between%201942-1952%20was%20also%20called%20the%20parity%20years%20where%20farmers%20got%20100%25%20value%20of%20their%20produce%20assured%20to%20them%20by%20government%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20how%20did%20the%20programme%20work%3F%20In%20principle%2C%20the%20USDA%20after%20analysis%20of%20agri-climate%2C%20market%2C%20demand-supply%20and%20carry%20over%20calculations%20suggested%20price%20floors%20for%20various%20agricultural%20commodities%20likes%20wheat%2C%20corn%2C%20rye%2C%20etc.%20to%20the%20Congress.%20The%20Congress%20then%20ratifies%20the%20price%20floors%20each%20season%20and%20announces%20them%20to%20the%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20agencies%20worked%20with%20the%20farmers%20directly%20and%20also%20through%20large%20farmers%E2%80%99%20co-operatives%20like%20the%20Burley%20tobacco%20co-operative%20in%20Kentucky.%20But%20in%20principle%2C%20before%20the%20sowing%2C%20every%20farmer%20received%20their%20growing%20quotas%20for%20their%20various%20agricultural%20commodities%20along%20with%20the%20price%20floors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20harvest%20time%2C%20farmers%20went%20to%20the%20co-operative%20market%20yards%20or%20grain%20elevators%2Fsilos%20or%20to%20the%20government%20grain%20reserves%20and%20deposited%20their%20produce%20and%20got%20it%20sealed%20and%20inspected%20by%20the%20government%20agents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20receiving%20the%20grain%20storage%20certificate%2C%20the%20farmers%20went%20to%20the%20bank%2C%20showed%20the%20certificate%20and%20secured%20a%20nine%20month%20loan%20equivalent%20of%2090%25%20value%20(the%20percentage%20could%20differ%20from%20year%20to%20year%2C%20but%2090%25%20is%20a%20good%20average)%20of%20the%20crop.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bank%20gave%20the%20farmers%20a%20non-recourse%20loan%2C%20which%20was%20guaranteed%20by%20the%20US%20government%20Commodity%20Credit%20Corporation%20(CCC)%2C%20and%20used%20the%20stored%20crop%20as%20a%20collateral.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20nine-month%20period%2C%20if%20the%20farmer%20is%20successful%20in%20selling%20the%20crop%20in%20the%20open%20market%20he%2Fshe%2Fthey%20return%20the%20loan%20amount%20at%20a%20low%20interest%20to%20the%20bank.%20If%20the%20farmer%20isn%E2%80%99t%20able%20to%20sell%20the%20crop%2C%20then%20the%20government%20takes%20over%20the%20crop%20collateral%20and%20transfers%20the%20produce%20to%20government%20reserves%20and%20the%20CCC%20pays%20the%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%20a%20small%20part%20of%20the%20agriculture%20produce%20landed%20in%20the%20grain%20reserves%2C%20the%20rest%20of%20it%20was%20brought%20and%20sold%20in%20the%20open%20market.%20The%20grain%20reserves%20acted%20as%20a%20bulwark%20against%20inflation%20and%20farmers%20were%20given%20growing%20quota%20based%20on%20carry-over%20reserves%20from%20the%20previous%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20scenario%2C%20the%20farmers%20receive%20the%20fair%20price%20and%20also%20the%20money%20required%20for%20the%20next%20sowing%20without%20failing%20into%20debt.%20The%20government%20by%20controlling%20the%20agriculture%20produce%20through%20reserves%20and%20supply%20management%20also%20ensured%20that%20industries%20get%20a%20regulated%20supply%20of%20raw%20material.%20This%20policy%20made%20the%20industry%2C%20farmers%20and%20consumers%20happy%2C%20as%20all%20were%20being%20dealt%20with%20fairly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20co-operative%20mode%20of%20this%20programme%20worked%20to%20keep%20millions%20of%20agrarian%20families%20in%20Kentucky%20growing%20region%20afloat.%20This%20model%20was%20promoting%20subsistence%20farming%20vs%20big%20farm.%20The%20small%20family%20farms%20could%20generate%20enough%20cash%20income%20from%20one%20or%20two%20acres%20of%20a%20tobacco%20crop%20only%20because%20of%20a%20price%20floor%20and%20guaranteed%20purchase%20programme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20result%20of%20this%20programme%20was%20that%20farmers%E2%80%99%20net%20incomes%20increased%20by%20115%25%20between%201942-1952%20when%20compared%20with%201920-1932%20period%2C%20increasing%20rural%20prosperity%20and%20restarting%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%201952%2C%20price%20floors%20over%20next%20four%20decades%20was%20lowered%2C%20and%20then%20ended%20due%20to%20corporate%20pressure%20and%20mismanagement.%20A%20full%20100%25%20of%20parity%20for%20agriculture%20as%20a%20whole%20was%20never%20achieved%20again%20after%201952%20though%20a%20few%20individual%20crops%20continued%20to%20achieve%20parity%20during%20the%201950s%2C%20such%20as%20burley%20tobacco%20and%20peanuts%2C%20according%20to%20USDA%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20end%2C%20millions%20were%20forced%20from%20the%20farms%2C%20the%20economic%20despondency%20reigned%20in%20once%20prosperous%20areas%20like%20Iowa%2C%20Kansas%2C%20Kentucky%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20unique%20thing%20about%20the%20programme%20was%20that%20it%20calculated%20price%20floors%20not%20on%20cost%20of%20production%20estimates%20but%20used%20a%20new%20base%20line%20method.%20They%20selected%20a%20base%20line%20period%201910%20to%201914.%20These%20years%20were%20selected%20because%20within%20this%20period%2C%20the%20price%20of%20the%20agricultural%20commodities%20rose%20at%20par%20with%20other%20market%20based%20commodities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEach%20year%20after%20was%20adjusted%20for%20inflation%20from%20the%20base%20line.%20They%20selected%20this%20formula%20because%20cost%20of%20production%20method%20is%20contingent%20on%20new%20technology%2C%20volatile%20agri-inputs%2C%20innovations%2C%20etc%20and%20hence%20can%20change%20drastically%20in%20the%20future.%20But%20the%20price%20of%20agricultural%20commodities%20over%20time%20will%20reflect%20general%20inflation%20and%20factor%20in%20newer%20production%20methods%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20summary%2C%20the%20programme%20worked%20on%20four%20general%20principles%20%E2%80%93%20first%20being%20the%20minimum%20price%20support%20floors%20which%20were%20backed%20by%20supply%20reduction%20quotas%20to%20meet%20supply%20and%20demand%20goals.%20Next%20is%20the%20guaranteed%20procurement%20and%20a%20ceiling%20price%20floors%20for%20the%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20case%20the%20agricultural%20commodity%20price%20reach%20a%20price%20ceiling%2C%20the%20government%20flooded%20the%20market%20with%20reserve%20grains%2Fproduce%20from%20the%20food%2Fgrain%20reserves%20stabilising%20the%20prices%20immediately.%20The%20whole%20system%20is%20based%20on%20a%20non-recourse%20loans%20and%20hence%20not%20a%20government%20subsidy%20for%20the%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Deal%20for%20India%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20big%20question%20now%20is%20%E2%80%93%20can%20this%20programme%20be%20adapted%20for%20India%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPotentially%20yes.%20And%20lets%20begin%20with%20institutions.%20India%20already%20has%20a%20robust%20agricultural%20extension%20system%20which%20is%20supported%20by%20government-backed%20grain%20procurement%20through%20FCI%2C%20NAFED%2C%20and%20other%20state%20agencies%2C%20much%20like%20post%20World%20War%20II%20USA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Fthe-men-behind-apmc-msp-and-procurement-6617277%2F%5C%22%3EAPMC%20(Agricultural%20Produce%20Market%20Committees)%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3Emandis%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20the%20price%20floor%20mechanism%20is%20already%20working%20in%20India.%20As%20for%20the%20financial%20credit%2C%20government%20has%20a%20robust%20rural%20credit%20system%20through%20the%20%3Cem%3Ekisan%3C%2Fem%3E%20credit%20card%20(KCC).%20And%20the%20final%20straw%20the%20government%20is%20already%20organising%20farmers%20into%20Farmer%20Producer%20Organisations%3Cb%3E%20(%3C%2Fb%3EFPOs)%20and%20co-operative%20societies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20the%20CACP%20(Commission%20for%20Agricultural%20Costs%20and%20Prices)%20which%20is%20setting%20prices%20floors%20for%2023%20crops%20each%20season.%20So%20our%20Indian%20agrarian%20system%20is%20very%20aligned%20to%20receiving%20such%20a%20policy%20intervention.%20To%20run%20it%20smoothly%2C%20additional%20investments%20in%20storage%20and%20marketing%20will%20be%20required.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Ffarmers-at-shambhu-border-say-we-now-feel-like-outsiders-in-our-own-country%5C%22%3EFarmers%20at%20Shambhu%20Border%20Say%2C%20%E2%80%98We%20Now%20Feel%20Like%20Outsiders%20in%20Our%20Own%20Country%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20farmers%20level%2C%20government%20first%20has%20to%20take%20stock%20of%20the%20KCC%20data%20and%20get%20an%20estimate%20of%20the%20number%20of%20farmers%20linked%20to%20the%20KCC.%20After%20this%20step%2C%20a%20through%20voluntary%20pilot%20programme%20will%20create%20clusters%2C%20potentially%20organic%20clusters%2C%20for%20enrolling%20farmers%20for%20various%20crops.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20can%20begin%20with%20wheat%2C%20rice%2C%20legumes%2C%20oilseeds%20and%20a%20programme%20for%20potatoes%2C%20onions%20and%20tomatoes.%20In%20the%20meanwhile%20the%20governments%20needs%20to%20stress%20on%20PPP%20(public-private%20partnership)%20to%20increase%20decentralised%20grain%20and%20perishable%20storage%20godowns%20linked%20to%20Food%20Corporation%20of%20India%20(FCI)%20and%20other%20state%20agencies%2C%20who%20can%20store%20the%20block%20level%20grains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20enrolled%20farmers%20upon%20harvest%2C%20will%20have%20the%20option%20of%20selling%20in%20the%20open%20market%20or%20else%20depositing%20the%20grain%2Fproduce%20to%20the%20government%20back%20godown.%20After%20depositing%20the%20grain%2C%20the%20farmers%20can%20get%20a%20certificate%20making%20the%20grain%20the%20collateral%20for%20a%20loan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFarmers%20can%20approach%20any%20government%20or%20private%20bank%20for%2090%25%20value%20loans%20based%20on%20the%20price%20floor%20for%20nine%20months.%20In%20case%2C%20the%20farmers%20find%20better%20price%20in%20the%20open%20market%20they%20can%20sell%20and%20repay%20the%20credit%2C%20interest%20and%20storage%20costs%2C%20else%20the%20grain%2Fproduce%20can%20be%20be%20sent%20over%20to%20the%20FCI%20and%20the%20state%20agency.%20After%20the%20sale%20of%20the%20produce%2C%20the%20bank%20or%20KCC%20provider%20can%20be%20repaid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20battle%20rural%20indebtedness%2C%20farmers%20should%20also%20be%20allowed%20to%20repay%20their%20KCC%20debt%20with%20crops%20or%20produce%20through%20this%20mechanism.%20This%20will%20also%20stimulate%20the%20agricultural%20processors%20and%20the%20so%20called%20middle%20layer%20to%20curb%20excessive%20profit%20making%20and%20trade%20fairly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20check%20overproduction%2C%20there%20can%20be%20a%20per%20acre%20limit%20of%20government%20procurement%20for%20certain%20commodities%20based%20upon%20the%20agro-climate%20conditions%20of%20the%20region.%20For%20example%2C%20there%20won%E2%80%99t%20be%20paddy%20procurement%20centres%20in%20dry%20parts%20of%20Rajasthan%2C%20but%20of%20legumes%20or%20oilseeds%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20FPOs%20and%20co-operatives%20societies%20linked%20directly%20with%20the%20programme%20would%20need%20to%20discipline%20members%20on%20production%20quotas%2C%20so%20all%20the%20members%20are%20benefited.This%20will%20be%20easily%20done%20as%2070%25%20of%20Indian%20farmers%20are%20small%20land%20holding%20farming%20families%20with%20under%20two%20acres%20of%20land.%20So%20their%20size%20makes%20them%20best%20suited%20for%20subsistence%20agrarian%20programme%20through%20which%20they%20can%20be%20plugged%20into%20the%20agrarian%20supply%20programme%20and%20also%20be%20given%20a%20cash%20income%20through%20price%20floors%20directly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENABARD%20can%20provide%20the%20refinancing%20for%20KCC%20loans%20or%20back%20the%20crop%20collaterals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20needed%20to%20implement%20this%20system%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolitical%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExpanding%20the%20agrarian%20institutions%20to%20grow%20into%20new%20roles%20of%20marketing%2C%20banking%20and%20storage%20is%20already%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20agenda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENAFED%2C%20Agricultural%20and%20Processed%20Food%20Products%20Export%20Development%20Authority%20or%20APEDA%20can%20also%20look%20for%20foreign%20markets%20for%20Indian%20surplus%20produce.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20linking%20KCC%20to%20price%20floors%20and%20crops%20as%20collateral%2C%20the%20government%20can%20highly%20ameliorate%20the%20agrarian%20distress%20by%20investing%20in%20an%20agrarian%20programme%20for%20supply%20management.%20If%20successful%2C%20this%20programme%20will%20also%20ensure%20MSP%20for%20farmers%20and%20food%20sovereignty%20for%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIndra%20Shekhar%20Singh%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eis%20an%20independent%20agri-policy%20analyst%20and%20writer.%20He%20was%20the%20former%20director%2C%20policy%20and%20outreach%2C%20at%20NSAI.%20He%20also%20hosts%20The%20Wire%E2%80%99s%20agriculture%20talk%20show%2C%20Krishi%20ki%20baat%2FFarm%20Talks.%20He%20tweets%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Findrassingh%5C%22%3E%40indrassingh%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709033423000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25131354%2Ffarmer-1.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fmsp-for-farmers-does-india-need-to-look-westwards-for-a-solution%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22By%20linking%20the%20Kisan%20Credit%20Card%20to%20price%20floors%20and%20crops%20as%20collateral%2C%20the%20government%20can%20ameliorate%20the%20agrarian%20distress%20by%20investing%20in%20an%20agrarian%20programme%20for%20supply%20management.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fmsp-for-farmers-does-india-need-to-look-westwards-for-a-solution%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22HTC%20CEO%20welcomes%20Apple%20to%20VR%20mar