g%20these%20milestones%20at%20different%20times.%20However%2C%20parents%20need%20to%20remain%20attentive%20and%20raise%20concerns%20if%20these%20milestones%20are%20delayed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F334578%2Fcoda-child-of-deaf-adult-indian-sign-language-isl%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHearing%2C%20an%20invisible%20aspect%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20often%20goes%20unnoticed%20until%20the%20child%20begins%20to%20speak%20or%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20doesn%E2%80%99t.%20A%20child%20who%20is%20not%20able%20to%20hear%20won%E2%80%99t%20be%20able%20to%20respond%20to%20noises%20or%20their%20name%2C%20and%20won%E2%80%99t%20start%20babbling%20and%20trying%20to%20imitate%20sounds%20by%20six%20to%20eight%20months.%20If%20parents%20are%20not%20aware%20of%20such%20childhood%20milestones%20they%20may%20not%20become%20aware%20of%20potential%20hearing%20issues%20until%20around%20the%20time%20the%20child%20reaches%20two%20years%20of%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20advancements%20in%20healthcare%20and%20technology%2C%20newborn%20hearing%20screenings%20can%20now%20detect%20hearing%20loss%20much%20before%20even%20the%20earliest%20milestones-based%20diagnosis.%20These%20screenings%20aid%20in%20the%20early%20detection%20of%20hearing%20problems%2C%20allowing%20for%20follow-up%20consultations%20with%20paediatricians%20within%20the%20baby%E2%80%99s%20first%20two%20to%20three%20months%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20World%20Health%20Organisation%20(WHO)%20estimates%20that%20there%20are%2063%20million%20people%20in%20India%20who%20suffer%20from%20significant%20auditory%20impairment.%20It%20further%20notes%20that%20up%20to%20five%20out%20of%20every%201%2C000%20babies%20are%20born%20with%20hearing%20loss%20or%20acquire%20it%20soon%20after%20birth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20the%20key%20to%20effective%20management%20of%20hearing%20loss%20is%20early%20identification%20and%20prompt%20trea